Document: AnimationNodeAnimation
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeanimation.rst
Summary: Describes the AnimationNodeAnimation class, a resource for AnimationNodeBlendTree that outputs a specific animation.
Inherits: AnimationNode < Resource < Object
AnimationNodeAnimation is a resource that can be added to an AnimationNodeBlendTree. It has a single output port and is used to specify which animation to play. This node is typically used as an input for other AnimationNode types that blend animations together.

Properties
animation (Animation): The animation to be played.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeAnimation
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeanimation.rst
Summary: This document describes the AnimationNodeAnimation class, which is used to play a specific animation within an AnimationTree.

Inherits: AnimationNode < Resource < Object

Description:
Plays a specific animation.

Properties:
Animation (StringName): The name of the animation to play.

Methods:
_get_animation_name() → StringName
_set_animation_name(animation_name: StringName)

This node is used to play a specific animation. It is a direct child of AnimationTree.

GDScript:
var anim_tree = get_node("AnimationTree")
anim_tree.set("parameters/Animation/animation", "walk")

C#:
var animTree = GetNode<AnimationTree>("AnimationTree");
animTree.Set("parameters/Animation/animation", "walk");
