Document: AnimationNodeAnimation
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeanimation.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the AnimationNodeAnimation class, which controls playback of a specific animation within an AnimationTree.

Property Descriptions
Property: advance_on_start (bool)
Default: false
Setter: set_advance_on_start(value: bool)
Getter: is_advance_on_start() -> bool
If true, on receiving a request to play an animation from the start, the first frame is not drawn, but only processed, and playback starts from the next frame. See also the notes of AnimationPlayer.play().

Property: animation (StringName)
Default: ""
Setter: set_animation(value: StringName)
Getter: get_animation() -> StringName
Animation to use as an output. It is one of the animations provided by AnimationTree.anim_player.

Property: loop_mode (LoopMode)
Setter: set_loop_mode(value: LoopMode)
Getter: get_loop_mode() -> LoopMode
If use_custom_timeline is true, override the loop settings of the original Animation resource with the value.
Note: If the Animation.loop_mode isn't set to looping, the Animation.track_set_interpolation_loop_wrap() option will not be respected. If you cannot get the expected behavior, consider duplicating the Animation resource and changing the loop settings.

Property: play_mode (PlayMode)
Default: 0
Setter: set_play_mode(value: PlayMode)
Getter: get_play_mode() -> PlayMode
Determines the playback direction of the animation.

Property: start_offset (float)
Setter: set_start_offset(value: float)
Getter: get_start_offset() -> float
If use_custom_timeline is true, offset the start position of the animation. This is useful for adjusting which foot steps first in 3D walking animations.

Property: stretch_time_scale (bool)
Setter: set_stretch_time_scale(value: bool)
Getter: is_stretching_time_scale() -> bool
If true, scales the time so that the length specified in timeline_length is one cycle. This is useful for matching the periods of walking and running animations. If false, the original animation length is respected. If you set the loop to loop_mode, the animation will loop in timeline_length.

Property: timeline_length (float)
Setter: set_timeline_length(value: float)
Getter: get_timeline_length() -> float
The length of the custom timeline. If stretch_time_scale is true, scales the animation to this length.

Property: use_custom_timeline (bool)
Default: false
Setter: set_use_custom_timeline(value: bool)
Getter: is_using_custom_timeline() -> bool
If true, AnimationNode provides an animation based on the Animation resource with some parameters adjusted.